## Overview

Fix Widget component to enable internal scrolling with frozen header for all widgets (especially Calendar Week/Day/List views).

---

## Problem Statement

### Current Behavior
- Week, Day, and List views scroll the entire page
- Widget header scrolls away when scrolling content
- Sidebars stay fixed (correct), but widget header should also stay fixed

### Root Cause
The Widget component (src/components/Widget.tsx) has:
```tsx
<div className="...">  {/* No height constraint */}
  <div className="...">Header</div>
  <div className="p-4 overflow-auto">  {/* overflow-auto but no height */}
    {children}
  </div>
</div>
```

**Issue:** The content div has `overflow-auto` but the Widget wrapper has no height constraint, so it grows to fit content, causing page scrolling instead of internal scrolling.

### Expected Behavior
- Widget should have constrained height (fill available vertical space)
- Widget header should be frozen (always visible)
- Widget content should scroll internally
- Like Excel frozen rows - header stays, content scrolls

---

## Proposed Solution

### Make Widget a Flex Container with Height Constraint

```tsx
<div className="border ... h-full flex flex-col">  {/* ADD: h-full flex flex-col */}
  {/* Header - frozen */}
  <div className="px-4 py-3 border-b ... flex-shrink-0">  {/* ADD: flex-shrink-0 */}
    {title}
  </div>

  {/* Content - scrollable */}
  <div className="flex-1 overflow-auto p-4">  {/* CHANGE: flex-1 instead of no constraint */}
    {children}
  </div>
</div>
```

**Changes:**
1. Widget wrapper: Add `h-full flex flex-col`
2. Header: Add `flex-shrink-0` (prevents shrinking)
3. Content: Change to `flex-1 overflow-auto p-4` (fills remaining space)

